videos.description: John Kelly extends the play with a stiff arm and spin move for a 24-yard gain that leads to a Vols field goal.
videos.headline: Kelly breaks multiple tackles on 24-yard run

videos.description: Rico Dowdle suffers an apparent leg injury in the first quarter against Tennessee.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (South Carolina RB Dowdle exits game with injury) 2017/10/14 ESHEET

videos.headline: South Carolina RB Dowdle exits game with injury

videos.description: Ty Chandler finds two big gaps and is able to break through for a 30-yard run that leads to another Vols field goal.
videos.headline: Chandler reverses field for 30-yard run

videos.description: Jarrett Guarantano laterals it to Josh Smith who throws deep to John Kelly where he can't make the one-handed catch in the end zone.
videos.headline: Kelly almost makes terrific catch in end zone

videos.description: Tennessee head coach Butch Jones says his quarterback Jarrett Gaurantano is managing the game well in his first start but needs to play better in the red zone.
videos.headline: Jones wants better red zone offense in 2nd half

videos.description: On third down, Jarrett Guarantano rolls out and is sacked by Antoine Wilder for a loss of 7 yards forcing the Vols to punt.
videos.headline: South Carolina defense gets drive-ending sack

videos.description: A.J. Turner breaks off a 20-yard run for a touchdown, but South Carolina's two-point conversion fails.
videos.headline: Gamecocks tie game with 20-yard TD run

videos.description: Tennessee's Jarrett Gauarantano attempts a pass to Brandon Johnson in the end zone for the win but it is broken up by Chris Lammons. South Carolina wins 15-9.
videos.headline: South Carolina defense comes up big with 1 second left

videos.description: South Carolina's head coach Will Muschamp says despite not having big plays his team controlled the line of scrimmage which was key in their 15-9 win over Tennessee.
videos.headline: Muschamp happy with how his team responded
